article.headline: Navy 60, Lafayette 44
article.story: ANNAPOLIS, Md. (AP) -- Greg Sprink had a game-high 23 points and eight rebounds to lead Navy to a 60-44 win over Lafayette on Saturday. The Midshipmen (11-7, 1-2) earned their first Patriot League win of the season. The Leopards (7-11, 1-2) turned the ball over eight times in the first eight minutes, and Navy opened the game with a 16-3 run on the way to a 28-16 halftime lead. Lafayette never trailed by less than 10 points in the second half. A layup from T.J. Topercer opened a 44-26 lead for Navy with 10:50 left. Sprink was a perfect 10-for-10 from the free-throw line and converted three 3-pointers. Adam Teague added 10 points and six rebounds. The Leopards shot a dismal 22.7 percent in the first half, but the team got a strong performance in the second from Matt Betley, who finished with 19 points and 12 rebounds.
